&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bengaluru.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vidarbha won their maiden Vijay Hazare Trophy title in the 2026 final held at Bengaluru, Karnataka.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 2026 Vijay Hazare Trophy final was held in Bengaluru, Karnataka.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vidarbha secured their first-ever title in the tournament.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The team defeated Saurashtra by 38 runs in the final.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The victory marked redemption after their defeat in the 2025 final.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vijay Hazare Trophy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A domestic one-day cricket tournament played in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Organized by the Board of Control for Cricket in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Contested by state and city teams.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Named after former Indian cricketer Vijay Hazare.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Board of Control for Cricket in India&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The governing body for cricket in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Manages domestic and international cricket tournaments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ponduru Khadi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ponduru Khadi from Srikakulam, Andhra Pradesh, has been granted the Geographical Indication (GI) tag.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ponduru Khadi is made from short-staple, hill-variety, pest-resistant cotton grown locally in the region.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The cotton used promotes chemical-free farming, supporting sustainable agriculture and eco-friendly production methods.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The GI tag ensures the recognition of Ponduru Khadi&amp;#39;s unique qualities, reputation, and geographical origin.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The GI tag is granted under the Geographical Indications of Goods (Registration and Protection) Act, 1999.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Geographical Indication (GI) Tag&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The GI tag is granted to products that have qualities, reputation, or characteristics inherent to their geographical origin.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It protects the traditional knowledge, skills, and products linked to a specific region, ensuring fair usage and recognition.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Ponduru Khadi&amp;rsquo;s Unique Features&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The fabric is handwoven, supporting traditional weaving techniques and the local artisan community in Andhra Pradesh.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is made from locally grown, pest-resistant cotton, highlighting sustainable and eco-friendly production practices.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Sustainable Agriculture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The cotton used in Ponduru Khadi supports chemical-free farming, contributing to eco-friendly and sustainable agricultural practices.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This approach helps reduce the environmental impact of cotton cultivation and promotes biodiversity in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Puducherry.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On February 12, 2026, the Ministry of Earth Sciences (MoES) and the Government of Puducherry signed a landmark MoU in New Delhi to advance marine research and blue economy initiatives.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; The agreement was signed between the MoES and the Department of Science, Technology and Environment, Government of Puducherry.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Areas:&lt;/strong&gt; The MoU covers six critical fronts including &lt;strong&gt;Sustainable Marine Fisheries&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Offshore Wind Energy&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Desalination Technologies&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Coastal Management&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Economy:&lt;/strong&gt; A major focus is on upgrading the &lt;strong&gt;Marine Spatial Planning (MSP)&lt;/strong&gt; framework to integrate resource mapping and offshore sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Validity:&lt;/strong&gt; The MoU has been signed for an initial duration of &lt;strong&gt;five years&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Support:&lt;/strong&gt; MoES will provide end-to-end technical support for setting up seawater desalination plants and establishing real-time ocean climate monitoring infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Deep Ocean Mission&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This MoU aligns with India&amp;#39;s broader &amp;#39;Deep Ocean Mission&amp;#39; which aims to explore deep-sea resources and develop technologies for sustainable use of ocean resources.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Signatories&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The agreement was signed by &lt;strong&gt;Dr. M. Ravichandran&lt;/strong&gt; (Secretary, MoES) and &lt;strong&gt;Dr. Sharat Chauhan&lt;/strong&gt; (Chief Secretary, Puducherry).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lymphatic Filariasis; 12.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Union Minister of State for Health and Family Welfare, Smt. Anupriya Patel, launched the first phase of the Annual Nationwide Mass Drug Administration (MDA) campaign for Lymphatic Filariasis elimination in February 2026.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The campaign is being implemented across 12&amp;nbsp;endemic states and Union Territories (UTs) to achieve the goal of eliminating Lymphatic Filariasis (LF).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The target states/UTs include **Bihar, Chhattisgarh, Jharkhand, Karnataka, Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh, Odisha, Uttar Pradesh, West Bengal, Gujarat, and Dadra &amp;amp; Nagar Haveli and Daman &amp;amp; Diu.**&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;India has set a target to eliminate Lymphatic Filariasis by **2027**, which is three years ahead of the global target (2030).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Mass Drug Administration (MDA)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strategy - Door-to-door delivery of anti-filarial drugs (DEC, Albendazole, and Ivermectin) to eligible populations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Exclusions - Pregnant women, children below two years of age, and seriously ill persons are excluded from the drug administration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Lymphatic Filariasis (LF)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Commonly known as Elephantiasis, it is a **Neglected Tropical Disease (NTD)** caused by parasitic worms and transmitted by mosquitoes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It impairs the lymphatic system and can lead to abnormal enlargement of body parts, causing pain and severe disability.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Jan Bhagidari&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Minister emphasized a &amp;quot;Whole of Government&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Whole of Society&amp;quot; approach to ensure every individual in endemic areas consumes the medicine in the presence of health workers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Morbidity Management&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Apart from drug administration, the government is also providing Morbidity Management and Disability Prevention (MMDP) services to those already affected by the disease.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anu Garg.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1991-batch IAS officer Anu Garg has taken charge as the first woman Chief Secretary of Odisha, a landmark event in the state&amp;rsquo;s administrative history.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;Anu Garg, an IAS officer from the 1991 batch, has assumed the office of the Chief Secretary of Odisha.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;Her appointment is historically significant as she is the first woman ever to be appointed to this top bureaucratic post in the state.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;She has succeeded Manoj Ahuja, a 1990-batch IAS officer, who superannuated from the service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;She is set to have one of the longer tenures in this position, as she is eligible to remain in office until March 31, 2029.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Manoj Ahuja&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was the outgoing Chief Secretary of Odisha whom Anu Garg succeeded. He is a 1990-batch IAS officer whose tenure was marked by exemplary leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Mohan Charan Majhi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He is the Chief Minister of Odisha. He publicly congratulated Anu Garg on her historic appointment, highlighting it as a reflection of the state&amp;#39;s commitment to excellence and empowerment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Chief Secretary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Chief Secretary is the highest-ranking civil servant of a state government. This official serves as the principal advisor to the Chief Minister and is the head of the entire state civil service.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Odisha @ 2036&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This is a long-term vision document mentioned by Anu Garg upon assuming office. It outlines the state&amp;#39;s development goals to be achieved by 2036, which will mark 100 years since Odisha was formed as a separate province.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
